England Reaches 124-8 on Opening Day of Second Cricket Test Against India

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-29T15:00:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-29/england-reaches-124-8-on-opening-day-of-second-cricket-test-against-india.html
England  was 124-8 at tea on the
opening day of the second cricket Test against India.  Ishant Sharma, Shantha Sreesanth and Praveen Kumar each
claimed two wickets as India took 6-55 in the afternoon session
at Trent Bridge in Nottingham. Sharma has taken 3-38, Sreesanth
is 3-49 and Kumar is 2-27.  Ian Bell  top-scored for England with 31 before edging to MS
Dhoni from Sharma. Stuart Broad is 6 not out and Graeme Swann
has no score.  England won the opening Test by 196 runs. It can overtake
India at the top of the International Cricket Council rankings
by winning the four-game series by two Tests or more.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  